There's an upstairs, possibly a roof, but I didn't see it myself. I did see a patio that comfortably seats three tables of <3. The staff seems capable, and moderately friendly, which is like the best friendly. You know what I mean, they're helpful, and knowledgeable, without being that overly, weird, bubbly that is just kinda fake. Great selection on draft beer, without being too...uppity. It's a pizza joint, and while that isn't really kicking down any doors, it hits the spot. They have a great happy hour price point, so check that out. Tuesday is trivia night. Get there on time, and make sure you have a space at the tables closer to the kitchen. This is where trivia host guy has his set up, and his speaker only blesses those in that area. (Which is a plus, if you aren't there for trivia, and don't want to hear mundane questions about something random no one cares about.) All in all, the place is cool. Check it out!

Decided to make a stop here to sit, talk, and have a nice pie. Even though it was busy, they had room for two more. Service was nice and did not seemed bothered that we stayed a little longer to continue our talk, but we compensated hopefully in our tip. Now to the good stuff. Beer and wine selections were as diverse and limited as any other place around, so if you are looking at just a bar - don't go here. Yet if you are looking at a pie that is full of flavor- this is the place. We ordered the largest one for two people. Needless to say, a box was needed as there was no way we were going to eat all of it. Partly due to the hummus appetizer we started with. That was both a good and bad call as we really did not need it, but it was very good. Enough for four or more people to enjoy as an appetizer. The pizza was a little dark, borderline burnt on the bottom, which made it easier to pick up by hand, but for some of us who like to eat our pies with utensils, cutting it was a little difficult. Overall, would I go again. Absolutely. I would leave off the appetizer, order the pie,and have one drink (or two). The roof top was closed, which disappointed us, but it was still a great place to go.

We were there today. Myself, my wife and our two kids with two friends from out of town. We ordered a large cheese pizza a salad and the artichoke dip. As we were eating our appetizer, my 7 year old son said he saw a rat moving across the air duct along the ceiling. We kind of blew it off, thinking he was imagining it. However, he is a very observant kid, and we shouldn't have disregarded it so quickly. After our pizza came, as we all talked and ate, a loud scream/squeal came from the wall beside our booth. It was undoubtedly the sound of a rat. We were all instantly freaked out and my son's claim became more believable to us. We all got up and couldn't really fathom the idea of eating any more, so we told the waiter what happened and paid the tab. He said, the manager wasn't in to talk to us but he took our drinks off the tab. We paid the tab and left. I understand that it's the city and rats are all over, but it's the first time I've ever had an experience like that in any restaurant. I doubt we'll be able to go back. It's just hard to get that kind of experience out of our head. The food was good up to that point, and the service was great!
